## Public-Safe Evidence Requirements

Each completed test should record:

| Field | Required |
|---|---|
| Test ID | YES |
| Test name | YES |
| Expected safe behavior | YES |
| Observed behavior | YES |
| Result label | YES |
| Public-safe evidence note | YES |
| Secrets excluded | YES |
| Remaining limitation | YES if applicable |

---

## Public Output Must Not Expose

Do not include the following in public evidence:

- raw paymentId
- raw txid
- wallet address
- recipient address
- access token
- service role key
- private key
- passphrase
- raw Pi API response
- raw database error
- stack trace
- environment variables
- sensitive customer data

---

## V13 Pass Requirements

V13 cannot be called passed unless:

- duplicate approve behavior has a clear safe result
- duplicate complete behavior has a clear safe result
- duplicate receipt/evidence behavior has a clear safe result
- paymentId replay fails secure
- txid replay fails secure when applicable
- paymentId / invoice mismatch fails secure
- Pi API timeout fails secure
- Pi API ambiguity fails secure
- durable state failure fails secure
- public verify unknown pair does not return active verified trust
- public verify mismatched pair does not return active verified trust
- access unlock guard still holds
- safe error scan passes
- remaining limitations are documented
- no production/audit/partnership claim is added

